; Permissions for the password-authenticated direct-connect DCV session.
; The direct dcvserver runs as root, so its console session is owned by
; root; the client authenticates as ${USER} (a different principal) and
; would be denied by the default "%owner% allow" rule. Access here is
; already gated by system (PAM) authentication — the OS password — so grant
; any authenticated principal full access to the session.
[permissions]
%any% allow builtin
